headline: AMCR Q2 Earnings Top Estimates, Sales Miss as Volume Decline Continues
summary: Amcor tops Q2 FY26 EPS estimates as acquisition-fueled revenues jump 68%, even as volumes decline for a third straight quarter.

headline: AVY Q4 Deep Dive: High-Value Category Growth and Tariff Impacts Shape Outlook
summary: Adhesive manufacturing company Avery Dennison (NYSE:AVY) missed Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q4 CY2025 as sales rose 3.9% year on year to $2.27 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $2.45 per share was 2.9% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
